description: Keep lint, test, and build logs isolated per command
alwaysApply: true
---

# Testing Terminal Isolation

- Run each verification command in its own terminal invocation.
- Do not chain verification commands with `&&` or `;` (for example `yarn lint && yarn test:unit` is not allowed).
- Keep these commands isolated for readable logs: `yarn lint`, `yarn lint:types`, `yarn lint:style`, `yarn test:unit`, `yarn build`, `yarn test:component`, `yarn test:e2e`.
- When reporting progress, list results per command in execution order.
